# ==============================================================================
# KAMPUNG SIBER RETRO WORKSPACE - HYBRID ENGINE OPTIMIZED RULES
# TARGET: Groq Llama-3.3-70b (PLAN) & OpenRouter Laguna-XS-2.1:Free (ACT)
# ==============================================================================

## 🚨 GROQ PLAN ENGINE CONSTRAINTS (CRITICAL: 12K TPM / 100K TPD LIMIT)
1. ULTRA-CONCISE PLANNING: When in planning mode using Llama-3.3, you must output blueprints in strict bullet points (max 5 lines). Do not dump large source code chunks, repetitive documentation, or theoretical explanations. Every token matters.
2. STATELESS ANALYSIS: Keep background explanations to an absolute zero to protect the 12K Tokens Per Minute budget from hitting HTTP 429 rate limits.
3. PRE-READ FILTERING: Never read massive raw files if only checking tiny layout definitions. Use precise search tools or read targeted line scopes.

## 🏗️ LAGUNA ACT ENGINE RULES (PRODUCTION-READY EXECUTION)
4. FULL STRUCTURAL OUTPUT: When the actor engine modifies, builds, or refactors code, always return complete functional code blocks, types, or file logic components.
5. ZERO LAZY PLACEHOLDERS: You are strictly prohibited from using lazy comments such as `// code remains the same`, `// ... rest of code`, or `// insert logic here`. Write out every clean script entirely for automated execution.
6. SURGICAL DEBUGGING: When a compilation or build crash occurs, isolate the root cause methodically. Provide a one-sentence breakdown of the bug, then immediately execute the fix.

## 📐 WORKSPACE ARCHITECTURE & DISCIPLINE
7. SEQUENTIAL EXECUTION ARCHITECTURE: You must process exactly ONE file at a time. Read, analyze, patch, test, and commit that file completely before moving to any other component. Never open multiple files simultaneously.
8. NEXT.JS 15 APP ROUTER COMPLIANCE: All new feature layouts must reside strictly within the modern Next.js App Router architecture ('src/app/'). Do not create legacy structure setups unless refactoring an existing specified file.
9. THE 500-LINE HARD CEILING: No single file or component in this codebase shall exceed 500 lines of code. If your code additions push a file past 500 lines, you must sound a warning and suggest breaking it into modular components under 'src/components/'.
10. SILENT FILE INTERACTION & GUI BAN: Run all file editing, creation, and reading operations silently via system calls. You are strictly forbidden from executing terminal commands that invoke graphical text editors or external browser GUIs.